        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 6 at 4:53PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 453 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southwest of Maljamar, or 29 miles east of Artesia, moving east
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Maljamar, Lea County Zip Franklin Memorial Airport, and Loco Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM MDT for southeastern
New Mexico.</instruction>
